<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="969" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.515/50: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Acting <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-29T18:00:00-04:00">October
                                    29, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>95. Procedure mentioned in your 164, October 25, 5 p.m. is considered
                            satisfactory by the Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
